-03-14T05%3A46%3A45\",\"srcSet\":\"/_gatsby/image/3e49f3fd2fc151880077fb64d17929a6/5438827cff0ffc7cdc1cd9835f1c2aa0/How-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D256%26h%3D71%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-14T05%3A46%3A45 256w,/_gatsby/image/3e49f3fd2fc151880077fb64d17929a6/3f2e3b9e81af3b03f3c9004a813860ad/How-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D512%26h%3D142%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-14T05%3A46%3A45 512w,/_gatsby/image/3e49f3fd2fc151880077fb64d17929a6/6f5763e162fca3e48c849db4e196883f/How-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-02.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-02.png&a=w%3D1024%26h%3D284%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-14T05%3A46%3A45 1024w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":1024,\"height\":284},\"alt\":\"How to Speed Up Magento 2 02\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1412 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"2\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4. Configure Memcached for caching.</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Another method for enhancing the speed of an eCommerce website is by minimizing the burden on the database. This can be accomplished by setting up Memcached, which is a cost-free and open-source caching system for in-memory objects. With the use of Memcached, commonly accessed database queries are cached in memory, which lowers the number of requests made to the database, thus optimizing the overall performance of your store. Magento 2 can effortlessly integrate with Memcached, and it is a recommended caching solution for large online stores that experience high traffic volume.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5. Utilize flat categories and products.</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>A common cause of slow performance in M2 sites is slow database read speeds. One solution to this problem is to enable the Flat Catalog feature.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1413 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:1024px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;217&#x27;%20width=&#x27;1024&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"3\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/6739ddcc618f638a0c4dd000bf0e2dc0/0c932c1f3ced9d9b67701028f89f7321/How-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-03.png&amp;a=w%3D256%26h%3D54%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-14T05%3A50%3A08\" data-srcset=\"/_gatsby/image/6739ddcc618f638a0c4dd000bf0e2dc0/0c932c1f3ced9d9b67701028f89f7321/How-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-03.png&amp;a=w%3D256%26h%3D54%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-14T05%3A50%3A08 256w,/_gatsby/image/6739ddcc618f638a0c4dd000bf0e2dc0/c886774ecb8d64a6b00d757c955a6122/How-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-03.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Speed-Up-Magento-2-03.png&amp;a=w%3D512%26h%3D108%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=202