</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Under the General tab, select Web.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Base URLs (Secure) section, you can add HTTPS URLs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">8. Use a lightweight and optimized theme.</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Selecting a lightweight and swift eCommerce theme can have a significant impact on the loading speed of your online store. When deciding on a theme for your eCommerce site, it&#8217;s crucial to weigh its effect on the overall performance of your website. Opting for a lightweight and rapid theme can curtail the amount of time it takes for your site to load, ultimately enhancing user experience and boosting customer satisfaction. Conversely, a weighty and slow-loading theme can have an adverse impact on your store&#8217;s performance, leading to higher bounce rates and lower conversion rates. To ensure peak performance, it is highly recommended that you opt for a lightweight and fast theme for your eCommerce store.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">9. Carefully select extensions.</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The selection of appropriate extensions for your Magento 2 store is crucial to maintain its efficiency. Many users tend to overlook the need to check for glitches in the extensions they use, which can have unfavorable effects on their store&#8217;s performance. To ensure optimal performance, it is vital to only use third-party extensions for your Magento 2 store that is free of any bugs.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">10. Optimize images for faster loading.</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Product images on your store site can slow down the performance of your Magento store if they are not optimized properly. To improve the speed of your Magento site, consider the following tips for image optimization:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Compress images to reduce their file size.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Utilize an image optimization module.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use PNG or SVG format for your store&#8217;s logo.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Use JPEG format for product images.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In summary, boosting the speed of Magento 2 necessitates a comprehensive strategy that encompasses optimizing server configurations, utilizing caching mechanisms, optimizing images, and reducing HTTP requests. In addition, updating the Magento 2 platform regularly and utilizing bug-free third-party extensions can also enhance your store&#8217;s performance. By implementing these tactics, you can considerably enhance the speed of your store and provide your customers with a smooth shopping experience.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-speed-up-magento-2/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-align: middle;width: auto;margin-left: 7px;'>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=How+to+Speed+Up+Magento+2+%2810+Easy+Steps%29+https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fhow-to-speed-up-magento-2%2F'style='display:inline-block' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img data-pin-nopin= true class='sfsi_wicon' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/Twitter_Tweet/en_US_Tweet.svg' alt='Tweet' title='Tweet' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div></div></div><div class=\"saboxplugin-wrap\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\" itemscope itemprop=\"author\"><div class=\"saboxplugin-tab